review_blob: Pure sweetness. This is a beautiful beer, it tastes a lot like Bells Hopslam. Excellent hop balance.
Very cloudy, lots of sediment. A good taste, but not very hoppy. Id drink it again, but its not something Ill be craving.

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: Advertised as a mild dark beer, and it lives up to it. Has a nice dark taste, but mild enough to drink some several.
Fantastic, drinking this from a cask. Good aroma is overtaken by deliciously hoppy taste. A lot like Bells Hopslam.
A buddy picked this up in Nashville over the weekend and brought back a growler. The hops dont overwhelm the malt in this beer creating a great balance.
A spicy IPA, not your typical hop fest. Sort of a grassy taste, but not too much so. I drink this a lot.
A beautiful beer in the sunlight to enjoy on UCBCs patio. Id give it 3 thumbs up if I had another hand.
Mikkeller did it again! Although the aroma isnt quite there, the taste is excellent, with good hoppiness and a spicy note.
This was the last of a four beer sampler from Ninkasi, and boy did I save the best for last. If I could get this regularly it would be one of my favorites.
This is 1 of my favorite beers. Its a great summer time session beer. It has good flavor but not too much that you cant drink several of them.

I was really looking forward to this. Ive had other Charleville beers that have been excellent. The initial aroma was wonderful, but was soon over powered by yeast. There was way too much yeast for an IPA, to the point that it settled at the bottom of my pint glass in a pile about the size of a quarter. Surely I got the bottom of the barrel?
A lot darker than I expected with little to no head. A very rich flavor, I imagine this beer would pair well with chocolate and berries.
I had this beer again and its making me love winter beers all over again. Too bad its spring now
beer_name: Southern Tier Old Man Winter Ale

review_blob: Definitely not what I was expecting from a Porter. A very complex beer, with tastes of fruit and nuts.
I love the UBCB beers, and this one is good, but it leaves me wanting more. Its not hoppy enough for an IPA to me, but that may just be the Chinook hop.
I love this beer. I wish it wasnt only a seasonal. My local store had a 2 6-pack per person limit. I had to go back multiple times.
